Forrest is a young (2-3 year old), 33 lb mixed breed pup looking for his forever home! Forrest does absolutely wonderful with other dogs, cats, and kittens alike. He is  !00% house and crate trained, neutered, HW negative, and up to date on all vaccines. 

Forrest came from an outdoor animal hoarding situation where he spent his entire life on a chain, along with 30 other dogs. Although he has excellent house manners (he is as easy going and low maintenance as they come), he is very shy to new people and will require a family who understands he needs time and patience to come out of his shell. Forrest is much more comfortable with other dogs around, therefore a home with another dog for him to bond with is a requirement. We will unfortunately not be considering homes without other dogs at this time. 

Forrest has great leash manners, loves to sun bathe, a peanut butter kong, and laying in his favorite bed. He has had limited exposure to children in his foster home.

Anyone interested in Forrest should complete an application found on our website angelasark.org. Once Forrest is adopted, the posting will be removed.

Our dogs are split between residence at our shelter, Camp Pawsawhile Retreat, and foster homes. Meet and greets are available by appointment only. Please complete an adopter profile to set up your meet and greet: http://coastalpetrescue.org/adopt/profile

Adoption Fees:
Kittens: $60, Cats (1 year plus): $50, Puppies: $250, Adult Canines (1 to 6 years): $200, Seniors (7 years plus): $100 (unless otherwise specified). Adoption fees are not a tax-deductible donation as allowed by IRS regulations. Adoption fees help to offset the cost of the pet's care incurred by Coastal Pet Rescue, which are generally 2 to 3 times the adoption fee amount.
Some special circumstances may change the fee; see pet's listing for actual adoption fee.

All Coastal Pet Rescue pets are current on shots, microchipped* and spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Adopters are responsible for any shots that may be due after adoption (particularly for kittens and puppies that must have three rounds of shots to be protected).

Microchip:
CPR has implanted a microchip as part of the adoption process and the chip is included in the adoption fee. However, some chip companies require a registration fee varying from $9.99 to $19.99. The registration fees are the responsibility of the adopter and are NOT included in the CPR adoption fee. Adopters may add this cost to their adoption fee to have CPR register the chip on their behalf.

30 Days Pet Insurance: 
As a Petfinder member, all adopters are entitled to a free 30 day insurance policy through PetFirst. Coastal Pet Rescue is not responsible for this policy. Adopters must call PetFirst’s toll-free number 855-710-7387 to activate the coverage. If adopters fail to call, the policy will not be activated.

animal.description:
Meet Bella!!! 
This cute this pup is searching for her forever home!! 
She’s almost 8 weeks old, and when it comes to her breed.... well we think there is some Norweigen Elkhound in there, some GSD, possibly even some Husky or Akita?. 
She’s got a nice thick undercoat and as she’s getting older it has really been lightening up. As a puppy her fur was almost all black, now she's a lighter tan. 

She’s a big girl! We estimate she’ll be 65lbs + when full grown. 

Bella is looking for an active household with other playful dogs and kids over 10 only. She can be rather mouthy so she is looking for an experienced handler to guide her and train her to be a well-behaved dog. 
She loves the water and loves being outside. 
She gets along with all dogs and cats. She does like to play a lot! So she may be too much for older dogs. 

All potential adopters are expected to complete an application and provide pictures of their yard, patio, and/or balcony making sure we can see the fence line and/or railing.  The application can be completed and submitted from our website - throwmeabonedogrescue.org - the link is found of the Adoption Process page.  Applications will be reviewed for approval before setting an appointment to come meet and possibly adopt the dog of interest.  In addition, those who live in a rental property are expected to provide proof that they are allowed to have a dog where they live.

Each of our rescued dogs has been de-wormed if necessary, de-flea'd (with topical treatment if old enough, and by medicated bath if too young), spayed/neutered, microchipped, is up to date on shots, and has been fully examined by a veterinarian.  In addition, each adopted dog comes with a starter baggie of the food it has been eating, a few treats for training purposes, a rawhide chew, a lead and collar, and a folder containing pertinent records.

animal.description:
UPDATE: Ginger has just had her left eye removed, she is healing very well and feeling so much better. There was severe glaucoma in the eye, pressure, and no vision. In addition she had pain from lack of dental care, and received a full dental, a few extractions, and now will have no pain in her mouth. Thank you to our awesome Medical Team!
Ginger is a beautiful 12 year old Siberian Husky and she is hoping to get out of the shelter and into a forever home that is just right for her. Ginger loves to be outside, she is healthy and happy, and has the more relaxed, independent personality. Ginger is your typical good natured Siberian with a mind of her own and a love for life. Ginger had been on a sled dog team in her younger years and loves to get up and go, but can not keep the pace like she use to. Ginger is use to being top dog on the team and will to best in a home with a male dog and with no small critters to chase. Ginger is now looking to settle down, with walks now and again to keep the blood flowing. But she really just needs a soft place to land and be a retired pampered pooch! Ginger is a real sweetheart looking for that special someone to share her heart with!
*If you are interested in adopting Ginger please call the shelter (509 662-9577) to set an appointment to meet her.

Phaedra is still very young at heart and has a lot of life and love to give! She is the sweetest, most affectionate girl you'll meet!

animal.description:
MEET SHAYNA!!

Underdog Rescue does not physically have this dog in its possession. She is currently located at Maricopa County Animal Care & Control, Animal ID Number A4504156.

Shayna has now been at the shelter for over 60 days and she is ready to go home! Many of the volunteers that have taken her out for walks say she is such a great dog. She walks nice and easy on a leash and still has a spring in her step for being 8 years old. She is affectionate and loves to be petted. She also knows "sit" for treats and will take them gently. It's a mystery why this pretty girl hasn't been adopted yet.

When Shayna sees another dog on the walking trail, she is curious and watches the dog but then continues on her walk. But when she sees another dog in a kennel barking at her, she runs up and barks at them too. If a dog is quiet in their kennel, she leaves them alone. So Shayna can be picky about her friends and needs a dog introduction if you already have a dog at home.

Shayna would make a great addition to a family with older children (12+). If you think Shayna could do well in your home, please come and meet her today! She'd love to go home.

NOTE: People who sign up for these appointments often no-show, and we have seen that you can generally show up and let them know you are there to meet this particular dog and the shelter will squeeze you in, except from 12-3PM or closer to the 6PM closing time. (Please know this is not a guarantee). If the dog is at risk, please ask for a supervisor to meet that particular dog.

*Please Note: This animal is courtesy posted for the Maricopa County Shelter; UNDERDOG RESCUE DOES NOT HAVE THIS DOG. MCACC is located at 2500 S. 27th Avenue, Phoenix. Different adoption fees/policy may apply. Please visit MCACC's website http://www.maricopa.gov/pets/locations.aspx for hours. You may also wish to call 602-506-7387 (PETS) and provide the animal's A# above to verify is still available.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Niko is a courtesy listed dog and not part of BFPA. Please contact Marissa at m_l_figueroa@yahoo.com to find out more about Niko and to meet him. DO NOT APPLY TO BFPA and also note that Niko is currently being fostered. in Greenville NC.

Niko is a super friendly, @two year old, red nose pit bull. He is currently 60 pounds but could be anywhere from 60-85 pounds. He gets along with other dogs but has not had any interaction with cats yet. He has been around children 10 years old and up and did good minus the fact that he likes to give hugs. We are working on that and he is doing better. He was around a week-old baby and when he heard the cry, he kept trying to see her but because he likes to give hugs, I have not yet let him in touching distance.

Niko is totally housebroken. During the day I usually take him outside every couple hours to play around and potty. He really wants to play but even more than that he just wants love and attention. He will lounge around all day if you want but shouldn't because he is a baby and needs play time. A fenced yard is necessary in his forever home so he can get his energy out in the yard. Niko could be an only dog or join a family with furry siblings that he would love to play with in the yard.

Niko is crate trained! He knows when I say" kennel up" to go in, he usually understands when I open the crate. When he is in the crate, if I'm still in the room, he is quiet, but if I am leaving him alone, he will cry for a little and try to break out. At night, most times he sleeps in his crate, but he loves to snuggle so occasionally he sleeps in the bed. We are working on leash walking and he still pulls some but is doing good.

Niko's favorite thing to do is run in the hallways of my apartment. He loves to run around and body wrestle. He is shy with toys, but we are working on that, he likes balls he can kick around. Niko is the sweetest baby I've met. He deserves a loving home, he has so many strong points : People friendly, dog friendly, ferret friendly, potty trained, crate trained, gives lots of kisses and cuddles. The absolute most perfect family pet.

DISCLAIMER: We hope you'll consider adopting NIKO. He is a courtesy listed dog. This means that he is not a part of or associated with Best Friend Pet Adoption (BFPA). The bio information listed for him was provided by his owner and not generated or verified by BFPA. Adoption arrangements will be a private arrangement between you and the owner. As with any dog adoption, BFPA encourages potential adopters to gain as much information as possible before adopting. This includes temperament testing and verification of vet records to ensure the dog is in good health, UTD on vaccinations and has been sterilized. For more information about this handsome dog, please contact m_l_figueroa@yahoo.com. DO NOT APPLY TO BFPA.

animal.description:
Meet Presley! Presley is around 1 year old and 60lbs. This hound dog is ALL shook up waiting to meet his future family! Presley has proved to be a lover, not the hunter. Unfortunately for him, that was his only crime, but enough for his owners to send him to doggie jail. You see, gun shots scared poor Presley, and therefore he was deemed not worthy of his home. This hunk a hunk burnin' love would prefer cuddles and walks, rather than loud bangs and searching for dead things. This "teddy bear" just wants love and a family of his own! No cats allowed is this guys castle!

Update 1/25/21 - Presley unfortunately tested positive for heartworm disease. He got this by being bitten by an infected mosquito. He is not contagious to other dogs (but all dogs should be on heartworm prevention monthly, year-round to prevent infection/reinfection). Underdog has started Presley on treatment for heartworm, and with proper after-care, he will fully recover. His adopter will simply need to bring Presley to scheduled treatment appointments and keep him CALM (with strict crate rest or supervised relaxation) post treatment injections (for 3 months). We provide adopters with instructions and will cover needed medication. We are seeking applicants who live in the greater Madison area, since crucial treatment and care (multiple visits over 2 months) are completed at our vet clinic, located in Madison. Dogs who are treated for heartworm have a positive likelihood of recovery when post-treatment instructions and rest are followed.

Interested in this sweet dog? Apply today at http://www.underdogpetrescue.org/dog-application

**Please note: Our animals live in foster homes throughout the Madison area. We do not have a shelter where animals are available for daily viewing. Applying is the first step in our process.**

Dogs from Underdog Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
Spay/Neuter
Rabies, Distemper, and Bordetella Vaccinations (as age appropriate-puppy adopters may need to cover some vaccine boosters)
Heartworm Test (for dogs over 6mo)
Microchip
Deworming
Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

Our adult dog adoption fee is $300. Our puppy (under 5 mo) is $375. Our senior dog (over 8 yrs) is $250.

*Please note that all breeds noted are estimates or best guesses. We very rarely have information on our animals' actual breeds since they often come to the shelters we work with as strays*

animal.description:
Meet Pavel! He is a small guy weighing in at a mere 20lbs. He’s around 3-5 years old-  he came from a hoarding situation in AL and is now safe in foster care. 
 He’s looking for a home willing to invest 1x love, knowing they’ll get 10x love in return.
 Pavel is a master of the side-eye and slow to trust. When he sees your demonstrated patience, calm, and love, he comes out of his shell and wants to cuddle. A lot!
 He has been showing more of his spunky personality day by day. He began as quiet and timid, spending time in his crate with the door open however he has become more adventurous. He loves dog puzzles and other canine enrichment activities. He has spurts of energy and then will cuddle by your side. He loves to be on your lap or giving hugs when you’ll let him. At night, he sleeps well in his crate. 
 Pavel never had a chance to be potty trained, and is working on it. He’s not keen on leashes yet, and should be considered a flight risk. He can jump a low fence. There’s a lot of spring in those surprisingly long legs!
 Pavel has interacted positively with our resident dogs. He is a smart and gentle boy who looks forward to being your very best bud and will happily learn tricks for Wisconsin cheese curds.

Interested in this sweet dog? Apply today at http://www.underdogpetrescue.org/dog-application

**Please note: Our animals live in foster homes throughout the Madison area. We do not have a shelter where animals are available for daily viewing. Applying is the first step in our process.**

Dogs from Underdog Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
Spay/Neuter
Rabies, Distemper, and Bordetella Vaccinations (as age appropriate-puppy adopters may need to cover some vaccine boosters)
Heartworm Test (for dogs over 6mo)
Microchip
Deworming
Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

Our adult dog adoption fee is $300. Our puppy (under 5 mo) is $375. Our senior dog (over 8 yrs) is $250.

*Please note that all breeds noted are estimates or best guesses. We very rarely have information on our animals' actual breeds since they often come to the shelters we work with as strays*

animal.description:
Meet Mila! Mila is around 10 
months old and 40lbs. 
"Look into my eyes and you’ll find the most brilliant, mesmerizing, arctic blue eyes looking back at you! I’ve also got little white socks on all my feet, as well as a snow-capped tail. I look fabulous and I know it!

I’m looking for a lifetime companion who can dedicate lots of love and attention to me. In return, I’ll provide your life with plenty of cuddles and many laughs, given my silly disposition. Around the house, I will follow you around, curious about what you’re doing. I’d probably be happy to help too, if you just teach me how. I'm still learning house manners so you'll have to teach me & keep an eye on me until I learn. I’m quick to learn what I’m permitted, especially if there’s food involved. Speaking of food, I’m not very picky about my food or water, which means sometimes I’ll lick your floor/oven and drink toilet water if given the chance. Cheerios have been a great training treat for me. I’m also still learning to not mouth on humans. 
 If you’re busy, I’ll generally spend my time sleeping on the couch or crate, and watching out the window. 
I’m still working on housetraining. I know to potty outside, but I need routine & schedule because I'm still learning. 

I did spend some time with other dogs in my previous home, and I seemed to get along with them alright. 

Outside, I’m pretty good on leash, though if there is something interesting I’ll go after it without thinking. I haven’t had any problems with passing-by strangers petting me. 
 I like playing outside regardless of snow on the ground. 
 As of now, I loathe being restrained inside of a car. I’ll cry and bark to let you know, so I’d appreciate you taking the time to teach me that everything is going to be okay when I’m in a car.

Interested in this sweet dog? Apply today at http://www.underdogpetrescue.org/dog-application

Magnus is a handsome male with piercing amber-colored eyes who just came into our rescue. He weighs 67 lbs and is 3 years old we were told. 
He was surrendered to us after his owners could no longer take care of him. He's very food motivated, so with a bit of good food and exercise he'll get to where his weight needs to be!

He enjoys the company of his foster dog siblings, but is fairly shy and submissive to them. He absolutely loves his chew toys, especially the heavy duty ones! When he's taking a break from the activities, he enjoys going back into his crate or hanging out with his foster parents on the couch. 

He loves to interact with people and will practically fall over with all of the tail wags that he uses to greet you with! He doesn't know how to give doggie kisses and instead just gently bumps his wet nose on faces.

Magnus has fairly good leash manners but will still need to go into an obedience and training program to ensure that he excels and that he and his forever home thrive together.  He is very active and is constantly using his nose to sniff around. He'll do really well in a home that loves to go on plenty of walks and hikes!

animal.description:
Talk about a superwoman! Koa is a 3 year old spayed female boxer/pit bull mix who weighs about 40 lbs. Koa's story started when she was spotted on the streets as a stray. She had obviously given birth recently and was scavenging for food so she could properly feed her babies who were snuggled safely in a den she dug for them. Koa was a wonderful mama and kept her puppies safe, fat, and happy until they all were captured and brought to safety. Now that her puppies are weaned and ready for their own families, Koa deserves a family of her very own. This girl is as sweet as pie. She is weary of new people at first, especially men, but warms up quickly. She just needs a little time. No time was wasted getting comfortable in her foster home. She was happy to walk around and check things out with a toy in her mouth. Koa has been good with other dogs, seems fine with cats, and even did well with the respectful kiddos she met! She'll need some patience as she learns about the finer things in life, but we don't think it will take her very long. Koa seems to be housebroken and has alerted her foster family when she has to go outside. We are head over heels for this beautiful girl and cannot wait to find her the perfect forever family to love and spoil her for the rest of her life... could it be yours??

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/
We are a foster based organization, so we do not have a facility to visit. Please read our FAQs to learn more: https://www.all4pawsrescue.com/faq
Follow us on Facebook for foster updates and a full list of our adoptable pets: https://www.facebook.com/all4pawsrescue/

animal.description:
AT PEPPERMINT PIG ANIMAL RESCUE, WE UPDATE ALL OF OUR PETS ON A REGULAR BASIS. 

IF YOU SEE ME HERE, I AM AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION. PLEASE READ MY BIO BELOW TO LEARN MORE ABOUT ME AND HOW TO APPLY TO ADOPT :)

Meet the A pups: Annika and Adler, 6 months old, Shepherd/Bully type mixes.

Available for Adoption!

These two adorable siblings are playful and so sweet and ready to find their forever homes! Annika and Adler have been doing great with learning manners and basic commands in their foster homes. They are housebroken, but still puppies, so they may still have an accident here and there if they don't get out side in time. They both love to play with other dogs and they are good with kids (5+). Annika and Adler have been living in separate foster homes and are doing great, they do not need to be adopted together. 

$195 Adoption Fee.

A $10.00 non-refundable application fee is required to submit your adoption application and will be deducted from your adoption fee if you adopt.

All Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue dogs are spayed/neutered, current on vaccinations, heartworm tested, current on heartworm and flea prevention, and microchipped.

Along with other criteria evaluated in the adoption application, a Fenced Yard is required to adopt. 

Please see our Fenced Yard Requirements tab on our website for more information, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/fenced-yard-requirements/

Adoption area for Annika and Adler is within 2 hours of Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue. 

Please see our Adoption Radius tab on our website for more info, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/adoption-radius/

TO CHECK AVAILABILITY of any of our adoptable animals, please go to our available pets tab, here: https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/available-pets-for-adoption/

All pets listed here are updated regularly to reflect their availability.

ADOPTION APPLICATION INSTRUCTIONS FOR PEPPERMINT PIG ANIMAL RESCUE:

Before completing the application, please read our ADOPTION PROCESS tab on our website, here: 
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/how-our-adoptions-work/

To complete our easy online adoption application, please visit our website at PeppermintPigAnimalRescue.org.

All adoption information and applications can be found under the ADOPTION CENTER tab.

Adoption events are held every Saturday in our thrift store from 1:00pm to 4:00pm. Please complete your adoption application in advance so our volunteers have time to screen and contact potential adopters.

IMPORTANT: All applications are reviewed in the order they are received and qualifications are based on best fit for each individual pet. A volunteer will contact you if you are selected for a meet with adoptable pet. Final approval is always made in person.

Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue is a no-kill rescue. Please consider sponsoring a pet or donating to our cause. Click the DONATE tab on our website to learn more about how you can help. THANK YOU !

For questions or inquiries on our adoptable pets, please feel free to contact our volunteer rescue team directly by submitting a Contact Form from our website, here: https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/contact-us/

animal.description:
If ever there was a dog that deserved the red carpet treatment it is King! This precious Pup holds a sad story behind his beautiful brown eyes...but regardless of his rough start to life, King has not let that break his sweet spirit. A remarkable dog, King has turned starvation and struggle into strength; his story is just beginning and our wish for him is the happily ever after he will find in a Forever Friend or Family!

King is still young...but wise beyond his years. He is hungry for attention and direction...a very intelligent learner, King already responds to instructions like sit, down, uh-uh/no, out of the kitchen and is quick to change his behavior with gentle correction. His desire to please his humans makes him a student with fast results - pets and love are all the positive reinforcement King needs to keep his training on track.

King loves people - he is also great with kids and other dogs too! He is excited to welcome his Humans home and has not shown any concerns with separation anxiety. He is completely house-broken and will ask to go out if he needs or wants some backyard/play time. King is also crate-trained, he likes to keep an eye on his People and prefers to sleep (in or outside his kennel) and stay close to them as much as possible. He is a constant companion of the best sort - always there for a snuggle or smile, he will make the perfect pup for anyone looking to add joy and fun to their home!

He loves baths, walks and naps. He walks well on a leash and with more instruction/training would be an amazing fitness partner. King though, is also always open to some snooze time too. He is an active and relaxed dog at the same time - best of all worlds, King wants love more than anything and will accommodate any of his Humans needs or daily activities.

This amazing pup deserves the royal treatment and we hope he finds that in you! Come apply for a meet-and-greet and I guarantee you will fall in love fast! I know we did - King will rule your heart and home with lot of Happy and Fun and be your loyal Friend for life.

 

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
Snow, hikes, mountains, and searching for my familyI love Colorado! I am Diana and my two puppies and I recently arrived from Houston. I am a German Shepard mix, petite in size. My foster mom thinks I am the best and she should know as I am her 43rd foster dog! I am a sweet dog that loves calm and loving attention. Just a whisper of my name and my tail wags uncontrollably! My foster mom thinks I am an old soul who is taking time to learn all that my new life has to offer. I dont have much experience with getting in and out of cars, stairs or sliding doorsbut I am courageously learning each and every day. Today was the first I took toys out of the toy box, how fun dog toys are! I love my foster dog sister even though her puppy energy can be a bit much for me. A home with an older or calmer dog probably would be my preference; or even if I were to be the only dog in a family would be fantastic. I have done really well with older kids (9+ years old) that know I am a calm and easygoing dog wanting more pets and loves rather than to play energetically. It is funny how the kids giggle when I gently place my paw on their arms reminding them that I could use a loving pet. 

I am so looking forward to meeting my new loving family that will patiently introduce me to all the wonder a Colorado dog life has to offersnow, hikes, mountains and most importantly love. 

*Homeownership Required! Breed experience preferred.

animal.description:
Aloha! Meet ‘Kailee.’ In Hawaiian, Kailee means ‘Sea & Sky.’ She is being fostered in FL. If you are interested in knowing more about Kailee after reading her biography, please complete an adoption application on the SLR web site and enter Kailee as the sweet, loving lady you would like to provide a forever home to. If you have already had your interview, the foster mom will contact you to answer any additional questions you may have.
 Kailee is a ‘Parti’ color (black/white/silver) She weighs 15 lbs., is approximately 10 years old, and has natural ears and a natural tail. This little lady is house trained. No crating for her! She is working on her leash training. Of course she is spayed and up-to-date on all of her shots. She lost several teeth during her dental and now the remaining teeth are pearly white. She is a mix but she does not shed. She is not an ‘Alpha’ dog and is even friendly to cats. Kailee will be best in an adult home only. She would be fine as an only dog but also enjoys the companionship of other dogs.
Kailee is blind and deaf. She needs a stable environment where the furniture stays in place once she is part of the family. Kailee learns her environment very quickly as she is very confident and smart and has learned to overcome her vision and hearing issues – one might say her IQ is in the gifted range! She loves to cuddle with her foster and stays close to ‘her person’ throughout the day.
Kailee is treat motivated and has learned the command to ‘sit.’ She also knows when it is time to have her leash put on and go for a walk. Kailee has learned various ‘touches’ and what they mean. She is now working on a new touch for ‘down.’ Kailee would like a forever home that would enjoy continuing with teaching her various commands. If you feel you are the Forever Home that Kailee is looking for, please complete an adoption application and enter ‘Kailee’ as the sweet lady you are interested in. If you have an active application, please e-mail jamosher@bellsouth.net



              Mahalo Nui Loa – Thank You Very Much

Go here to see a video or Kailee - https://youtu.be/C9p7uqXvGLM

animal.description:
A brave little rescue named Bandit is being fostered in Lexington SC. If you are interested in Bandit, fill out an adoption application online and list him as the particular dog you are applying for. Already submitted an application and had your interview, then contact your state interviewer to request more information.
Bandit is a 10 month old male Mini Schnauzer. He weighs 14 lbs, has natural ears, a docked tail, and is gray in color. Bandit is up-to-date with his shots, on Heartworm Preventatives and is neutered. He was owner surrendered due to his lack of vision.
Bandit has retinal dysplasia in both eyes which has caused him to be have limited vision. He has been to an eye specialist. The specialist explained that retinal dysplasia is an inherited degenerative disease of the retina. It is passed from the parents to their offspring. There is no cure or treatment for retinal dysplasia. Fortunately, this is not a painful condition. Bandit still has some vision, and it is recommended that he be on a prescription oral retinal supplement to help slow further deterioration of the back of the eyes.


Make no mistake, this does not slow this energizer bunny down. He is all puppy. And, as a puppy, he will get into things he shouldn’t. So firm boundaries are a must. Bandit should be with adults only or a home with older children who will respect his disability. With his limited sight, Bandit startles easily. He will bark at the slightest noise until he is moved away or distracted. Bandit needs continuity (the same schedule daily). He needs an adopter who works from home or is retired.

Bandit will do best with another dog in the home, a guide dog per se. A fenced yard is a must. The eye specialist claims this will give him security and some independence.

Let’s recap Bandit’s requirements for adoption:
• Accept a special needs rescue/Oral supplement prescription runs $75 to $90 every three months
• Home with adults or adults with older children
• Another dog in the home
• Fenced yard
• Willing to work and train with Bandit/Strong pack leader
• Patience and more patience

If you can provide for Bandit and give him the human love and kindness he deserves,
then apply today.
Let this Bandit steal your heart!

animal.description:
In early November we took in a dog who was severely shut down, unable to be removed from her kennel at the NYC city shelter, or even be collared and leashed. She was scheduled to be euthanized but we knew we just needed to get her out of the shelter. SWEET TART, renamed SWEET TEA, was petrified of being outside and showed signs of living with a dominant person who was likely a recluse or a shut in.

Today, two months later, we are thrilled to share that we are officially looking for a for SWEET TEA! She has been rehabilitated enough that she can be placed with an adopter willing to help her grow to her full potential! 

SWEET TEA has recovered beautifully from surgery to remove 21 rotted teeth, most with exposed nerve. Living a pain free life has helped her open up and take in more of the world. Thanks to her incredible foster mom, Opal, SWEET TEA, started venturing outside into her backyard at the end of December. We suspect SWEET TEA had not been outside in years. She was only using indoor weewee pads to relieve herself, which she’d been trained to do. These days she heads outside for about 90% of her potty breaks and lingers to explore a bit! The video  may not seem like much but when you consider her story, it’s a major mountain for her!

WHAT DOES SWEET TEA, 50 lbs., 9-10 yrs, NEED? 
* Quiet neighborhood or rural community with a fenced in yard. She is not yet able to tolerate a leash so the yard is important as her new owner will need to be patient and understand she may take a long time to get used to a leash, if ever. SWEET TEA will need, and only wants, a small, quiet world.
* Low key, calm home. SWEET TEA is a senior with overall low energy. A calm, quiet home (no kids) with a person or people who like to hang out at home and who are low key is ideal. 
* Pets? SWEET TEA does not appear interested in other dogs. While she could prefer to not interact with other dogs (she was uninterested in our helper dog, Joey, when she met him) this could change as she settles into her new life.

For more in her story visit #AdoptSweatTeaMBC 
Email elli@mrbonesandco.org with questions.
To apply to adopt within driving distance of NY state, head www.mrbonesandco.org/adopt

#AdoptSweatTeaMBC #OneLuckyPup #RescueistheNewBlack

animal.description:
AT PEPPERMINT PIG ANIMAL RESCUE, WE UPDATE ALL OF OUR PETS ON A REGULAR BASIS. 

IF YOU SEE ME HERE, I AM AVAILABLE FOR ADOPTION. PLEASE READ MY BIO BELOW TO LEARN MORE ABOUT ME AND HOW TO APPLY TO ADOPT :)

Meet Kobe:: 2 years old, 60 pounds, Neutered Male Bully/Staffy mix.

Available for Adoption!

Kobe is literally the best boy you will ever meet! He is a GORGEOUS light Brindle color and he is a total baby, he absolutely adores all the people he meets and he loves to give you all of his affection and snuggles. Kobe is housebroken and does well if left out of the crate when his people are gone. He doesn't chew anything and just waits patiently for you to return. He has amazing in-home manners and would never beg for table food :) Kobe loves to go on walks and he is doing great with ignoring the other songs who pass. Kobe is very selective of his dog friends and would do best as the only dog in the home so he can be sure to have all of your love and attention to himself! Kobe is the biggest lover of people, but is just not a big fan of having other fur friends. Due to his intense snuggling abilities, any children in the home should be 10+ :) 

$145 Adoption Fee.

We'll be looking for large dog experience for Kobe, no otherdogs in the home.

A $10.00 non-refundable application fee is required to submit your adoption application and will be deducted from your adoption fee if you adopt.

All Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue dogs are spayed/neutered, current on vaccinations, heartworm tested, current on heartworm and flea prevention, and microchipped.

Along with other criteria evaluated in the adoption application, a Fenced Yard is required to adopt. 

Please see our Fenced Yard Requirements tab on our website for more information, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/fenced-yard-requirements/

Our adoption area, unless otherwise specified in their bio, is within a two hour radius of Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue for adult dogs, and within a one hour radius for puppies. 

Please see our Adoption Radius tab on our website for more info, here:
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/adoption-radius/

TO CHECK AVAILABILITY of any of our adoptable animals, please go to our available pets tab, here: https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/available-pets-for-adoption/

All pets listed here are updated regularly to reflect their availability.

ADOPTION APPLICATION INSTRUCTIONS FOR PEPPERMINT PIG ANIMAL RESCUE:

Before completing the application, please read our ADOPTION PROCESS tab on our website, here: 
https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/how-our-adoptions-work/

To complete our easy online adoption application, please visit our website at PeppermintPigAnimalRescue.org.

All adoption information and applications can be found under the ADOPTION CENTER tab.

Adoption events are held every Saturday in our thrift store from 1:00pm to 4:00pm. Please complete your adoption application in advance so our volunteers have time to screen and contact potential adopters.

IMPORTANT: All applications are reviewed in the order they are received and qualifications are based on best fit for each individual pet. A volunteer will contact you if you are selected for a meet with adoptable pet. Final approval is always made in person.

Peppermint Pig Animal Rescue is a no-kill rescue. Please consider sponsoring a pet or donating to our cause. Click the DONATE tab on our website to learn more about how you can help. THANK YOU !

For questions or inquiries on our adoptable pets, please feel free to contact our volunteer rescue team directly by submitting a Contact Form from our website, here: https://peppermintpiganimalrescue.org/contact-us/

Meet lovely Lulu! She has a gorgeous, shiny black coat and an adorable face that will light up your life! She is a sweet girl with soulful eyes and awesome ears. All she needs is a permanent place to call home. Lulu loves to play. She thinks other dogs and children make great playmates. She has not had a previous home with cats, so she is unsure of how she feels about them. This girl will need the support and commitment of her forever family to continue to practice good behavior, house breaking and her commands. Lulu aims to please, so with treats and lots of positive attention, she is sure to continue to work on all the skills needed to be a good girl! Lulu is ready to meet the family of her dreams.

If interested in Lulu, please email to inquire at: SCREENING.FETCHINGHEARTS@GMAIL.COM OR COPY LINK BELOW TO APPLY AND FILL OUT AN APPLICATION: https://www.fetchingheartsrescue.org/adoption-form-online
to fill out an application.

Unless otherwise indicated, all dogs adopted through Fetching Hearts have received the following before being available for adoption:

Thorough veterinary examination.

All routine annual vaccinations, including Rabies, DHLPP, Bordatella (Kennel Cough), Heartworm Test, Fecal Test, Deworming, Microchip, Flea and Tick Prevention and Heartworm Prevention.

Spay/Neuter.
All dogs are quarantined for two weeks outside of the shelter (puppies four weeks) to ensure they don't break with disease.

VETTING NOTE: Fetching Hearts Rescue completely vets our dogs thoroughly to the best of our knowledge based on communication with our Southern Vets. If anything is brought to our attention, we treat the dog. After adopting the dog, you will be responsible for following up with all vetting going forward.

HEARTWORM NOTE: Dogs who were treated for Heartworm can test positive up to 4-6 months after last treatment. All dogs are immediately put on Heartguard/Ivermectin following the treatment to kill the Heartworm larvae. All dogs should be re-tested after 5-6 months from the last Heartworm treatment.

animal.description:
Pamela is an approximately 3-4 year old female German Shepherd mix who weighs approximately 47 pounds.   Pamela came into Cafa from Forrest Hill Heartworm negative and with 3 adorable puppies.  She is an amazing girl.  Very sweet and smart.  Loves making new friends. Due to her breed we are not able to consider rentals.

Adoption fees details: 
Puppies - Adults $ 550, Seniors $375. These adoption rates include transport from Alexandria, Louisiana to designated New England adopter pick up locations and NE foster homes using either Rescue Road Trips, Pets LLC or CAFA Transport. If you do a search you will see that this is a very reasonable adoption fee and comparable to other rescues. Adoption fee breakdown:Adoption Fee:   $  365.00Transportation Fee:  $ 185.00MA and NH only--Quarantine fee if applicable:  $125.00

Medical details:
All our dogs are altered (spayed or neutered), DHLPP, rabies, Bordetella, Heartworm tested with negative test results, microchipped, treated for parasites and on monthly heartworm and flea and tick prevention. A health certificate is issued by a licensed Louisiana veterinarian.

Adoption details:  
In some instances, a meet and greet is not possible before adoption unless we have a foster home in New England available. Available for a Meeting confirms the dog is in a NE Foster home and available for a meeting in the city state provided.  Most times our dogs get adopted before a foster home becomes available - and if so, they go straight to adopters home. Foster parents talk to adopters and feel confident that this will be a match before our dogs are transported up. Also if by some chance it is not a match we have a safety net in place as we ask that adopters to let us know that it is not a match and we direct you to take the dog to a foster home or boarding kennel once that is arranged. If necessary, we will ask you to foster the dog until a foster home can be arranged. 
Transport details:Rescue Road Trips (rescueroadtrips.com), Pets LLC (petsllc.net) or CAFA Transport will deliver our precious pups on commercial rescue animal transport to designated locations.  The fee is 185.00 which IS INCLUDED in your adoption fee already.**Rescue Road Trips, was featured on The Today Show - view it at http://www.today.com/video/today/55034556#55034556

MA and NH RESIDENTS:
If you are a Massachusetts or New Hampshire residence, an additional fee of $125.00 will apply due to State quarantine fee requirements. If the dog is in a foster home in MA or NH, this fee will be added in the adoption fee regardless of where the adopters home is located making the total adoption fee $675.00 for puppies and adults $500.00 for Seniors, otherwise the full adoption fee for all other states is $550.00 for puppies and adults and $375.00 for seniors. This includes a 48 quarantine, recheck by a MA licensed veterinarian, and issued a MA health certificate.

Visit all our available dogs at www.cenlaallianceforanimals.comWe update and add dogs frequently.

We hope to help make a difference in a rescue dogs life into loving responsible homes.

animal.description:
Due to COVID-19, CITY DOGS is currently doing adoptions by APPOINTMENT ONLY. Please visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to request a meet and greet! 

Questions? Email: citydogs@city.cleveland.oh.us | Call: (216) 664-3476
Visit: 9203 Detroit Avenue Cleveland, OH 44102

Hours:
10 AM - 3 PM Monday, Wednesday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday
10 AM - 6 pm Tuesday & Thursday

Fee: $61 | Includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, license, 30 days free pet insurance (when registered upon adoption)

The CITY DOGS mission is to increase adoptions from the City Kennel by changing the image of the pit bulls who make up the majority of the kennel population, by preparing all adoptable dogs in the kennel for lives in loving homes and by creating as many opportunities as possible for the public to meet and get to know our dogs for the terrific pets they are meant to be.

Our Adoption Process...
Here's a little about how things work:
All of the CITY DOGS posted for adoption are available for direct adoption from the kennel, unless noted otherwise. You must schedule a meet with a dog in advance - we are not currently accepting walk-ins. Please look online first to see if there are any dogs you think would be a good fit for your home before scheduling a meet. To get the process started, visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog and fill out the form. One of our adoption counselors will get in touch to schedule and confirm your meet! At the kennel, an adoption counselor will introduce you and your family to the adoptable dogs, share information we know about them, and discuss our suggested ways for successfully integrating a new dog into your home. You are welcome to meet multiple dogs. If the dog you adopt is already fixed, he or she may leave with you that day - otherwise, the dog can go home after receiving the spay or neuter surgery.)

About Our Dogs: All available dogs have gone through a behavioral and medical assessment. This assessment is a snapshot of who the dog is at that given time. We cannot make any guarantees with regard to behavior, temperament or health of any City Dog once they are in the home. Most of our dogs are picked up as strays, so we do not know what kind of home environment they were living in (i.e. with kids, other dogs or other cats), nor do we know if most of them are house trained. Everything we know about them is based on volunteer and staff observations. We do have some dogs in foster homes, where they will have more information about how the dog is in a home environment. It is very hard to tell with certainty whether or not a dog will be good with kids, cats or another dog. If you have kids in the home or another dog, we do require that they be present for a meet and greet with the dog you are considering for adoption.

Heath/Vaccinations: Dogs that are adopted directly from the kennel need to go to your personal vet within two weeks of leaving the kennel. All dogs receive their DAPPL, Rabies, and Bordatella vaccines, though you may be required to get follow up boosters. All dogs come microchipped and with a Cuyahoga County license.?

animal.description:
Duke / Male / 9 Months / 60 lbs / Great Pyrenees x Catahoula Mix / Toronto

Meet Duke! Duke is as lovable as he is beautiful. Unfortunately this handsome guy was given up when his original family couldn’t support his needs. He needed training as all puppies do – and has since blossomed into a special dog. He needs a family who is committed to his ongoing training and ready to help expose is true potential!

Duke doesn’t know his own size and considers himself a lap dog! His fosters describe him as goofy, active, submissive, affectionate, cuddly and playful. Duke is looking for an active family with lots of time to take him on outdoor adventures. He would be a great second dog to an equally playful canine pal. Duke is the definition of a gentle giant and will make a special addition to one lucky family.

Duke is all over the people he trusts – but it takes time to earn that with him. With his foster parents he is constantly asking for cuddles and pets. He adores the companionship of his trusted humans. When new people enter the home he will bark or growl to protect his space. He is still learning that humans mean no harm and his socialization will be an ongoing effort. It took him approximately one week to warm up to his foster mom so potential adopters should have realistic expectations. He is particularly protective in the home and prefers to meet new people outside. When he is ignored and able to ensure there is no threat, he warms up very quickly.

Duke is a HIGH energy boy and has an extensive exercise routine to keep him balanced! He gets up for the first time at 7am, and goes out for his first potty break. After breakfast he goes for his first walk of the day that typically lasts one hour. Around lunch time he will get his second walk, and third walk is after dinner. His final walk of the day is usually around 9pm and is around 30 minutes in duration. Throughout the day his foster family also provides him with various forms of mental stimulation to keep his brain busy and focused. Potential adopters would do best to stick to a similar routine to ensure his success. It needs to be understood that he will need a minimum of 3-4 hours of exercise per day, not counting additional mental stimulation. He is not left alone much during the day but sometimes takes a few minutes to settle in his crate. With his current schedule, he is fully potty trained.

Duke is smart and would benefit from a family committed to daily training. He thrives with structure and a predictable schedule. He needs support with leash training and basic obedience commands. Although he has picked up sit, paw and recall quickly, he has the potential to learn so much more. Duke has done well with leash training but needs a strong handler as he pulls when excited. He can be reactive when he sees something that startles him, so will need consistent redirection. He is eager to learn and catches on quickly to everything he has been taught so far.

Duke’s ideal family would live in a detached home, outside of the city. He would do best with a fully fenced back yard so he has a secured green space to run and play. He is a loud alert barker so he will not be suitable for an apartment. He thrives with a consistent and predictable routine. He can be skittish and is labelled a flight risk, so even in his back yard will need to be supervised. Duke is dog selective but with proper introductions and supervision he would do well as a second dog. He has not been tested with children but based on his nature would prefer dog savvy children that are ages 10+. Duke is only looking for cat free homes (he will chase them).

If you’re interested in adopting Duke please apply at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/adoption-info#adoption-form

Duke’s adoption fee is $850. To learn more about our adoption fees and the adoption process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/about-us#about-faqs.

If there is a certain animal you want to meet at one the events please fill out a preadoption application to directly contact their foster family or check our Facebook page to see if they will be there! Their event attendance is based on the availability of their foster family.
Home visits (video tours or in person) are required for all dog adoptions. All of our cats and dogs are INDOOR pets and are NOT to be left outside unattended (even in a fenced yard), or running loose! 2/2/21 12:49 PM

animal.description:
Sheba had a rough start and came to us injured, sick, and afraid. But with a little TLC, she has flourished into a sweet, playful pup! She is the definition of a Velcro dog, if she could lay on her foster parents all day long, she would! She does very well with other dogs, but is easily intimidated and prefers to play with her 2 legged family. Sheba is happy to snuggle for hours, but also loves chasing a ball in the backyard, or going for walks. Because of her past, she is timid when meeting new people, but quickly warms up with a few treats! If you are looking for a loyal, loving companion, Sheba is your girl!!

If you are interested in learning more about this dog, please complete an application by visiting http://www.floridaurgentrescue.com/adopt.

***Please note that we are a volunteer run organization, and due to the large volume of applications, inquiries, phone calls, emails, and messages received we may not be able to provide a detailed, personal response to every single one. For that reason, formal applications will be given priority over the aforementioned.***

The adoption fee for dogs 6 months and older is $150; this includes the spay/neuter, microchip, and current vaccinations as of the date of adoption.

animal.description:
"Once you decide to follow your life's purpose, you will only need to pack one thing: your heart." It is a good thing that I have such a big heart because it means I am all ready to pursue my life's purpose: being the best friend you will ever know! My name is Roxana and I am a 2.5 year old, 55 pound Pit mix girl. I am a calm and reserved girl who enjoys hanging out with my people, whether it's at home, in the car, or out on an adventure. I am very smart, so I am already house trained, crate trained, and I even know some basic commands, like "sit." I am such a sweetheart that I also get along great with other dogs, cats, kids, and even guinea pigs! So, what do you think? Do you think our purposes are meant to intertwine in forever happiness together?

My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description:
This beautiful Husky girl with the piercing blue eyes is Sky SCAS.

Sky was originally a rescue dog who came from a shelter. A lady had found her running with a heavy chain around her neck and took her in. She surrendered Sky to the local shelter and this couple rescued her from there where she thought she would live happily ever after.

Sky is 5 years old and 77 lbs, housebroken, walks on a leash, and is fully crate trained. Sky would love a big fenced in yard, since she is very active, and is used to being outside all day playing and running. She LOVES playing ball so hopefully her new home will have some for her to play with. Sky gets along with other dogs, but her owner said she won't let Sky play with her small dogs since she plays too rough with them although Sky likes the little ones. She likes children too, but is not a fan of cats.

If you are interested in Sky, please fill out an application at www.ehrdogs.org and be sure to ask for her by name, SKY SCAS!

animal.description: This is what "Nevaeh" looks like in a home. Shes deaf and needs to be the ONLY dog but guaranteed perfect with kiddos and okay with cats. She needs atleast a 4 foot fence because she will run away and not great on a leash. I rescued her from the shelter/euthanasia at 7 months old. She has been in and out of a home 5 times. Each time was for different amounts of time ranging from a week to a year. Each time she was sent back was due to pregnancy, divorce, her tail hurts (which is now gone), she won't get along with other dogs (absolutely no other dogs can be with her and this is always made very clear!) and a few other terrible reasons. In those times, she also was lost a few times and ended up in the shelter. So many times I thought I'd never see her again. I won't change that again so dont bother inquiring if you can't secure a runner and or handle a special needs dog. She's a great dog that can't hear and would love a home to retire in. She's now coming up on 7 years old.

animal.description:
Blueberry is a 5.5 year old Red Heeler/King Charles Cavalier mix with a chill, happy personality. She loves to go for walks, chase after toys and most of all - play fetch!. Affectionate and quirky, she:
•	Is house trained
•	Is good with other dogs
•	Is 34 pounds
•	Walks nicely on a leash
•	Enjoys going for car rides
•	Loves to hike
•	Is medium to high energy
Blueberry still has the athleticism to rival a younger dog, but with age she has pleasantly mellowed and is a well mannered companion. She will thrive in an environment that is peaceful but still fairly active. Although she can certainly enjoy a cuddle session, this smart lady loves to DO things and will enjoy a family that likes to take her places and share their world with her.

Blueberry is spayed, vaccinated, microchipped, and heartworm negative. 

For more information about Blueberry or our shelter please call us at (830) 693-0569 or visit our website at highlandlakescaninerescue.org 

If you would like to schedule a meet and greet with Blueberry or any of our dogs, please fill out an application at highlandlakescaninerescue.org/application-for-adoption

Meet Blake!  He is a 8 year old male Border Collie mix that is looking for a forever home.  He is a classic collie - loyal to the end.  He cares about your every move and wants to take care of you.  Blake doesn't like to be left alone, so he would an adopter that is home a lot and in a home without small children.   He is potty-trained and loves to nap in a comfy bed. He is a lovable boy that enjoys pets.

The NAWS Dog Adoption Program operates as a rescue versus a shelter.  We believe in matching the right dog with the appropriate family based on each specific dog or family's needs.  To achieve this, we believe in spending the appropriate amount of time with each family to allow for enough interaction time with potential adopters.  This cannot be achieved if people stop by unexpectedly to meet our dogs.  Please e-mail Stacy at stacy@nawsus.org to setup a day or time to meet with one of our adoption counselors and our potential adoptees.  Thank you!

animal.description:
Meet 8yr old and 85lb silly guy Chulo. Poor guy found himself at a high kill central valley shelter super confused after his family passed away. He was in rough shape but after good diet and love he is looking great. He is very friendly and seeks attention. He has a great personality and loves everyone. He is very dog social both big and large. His original home he lived in had cats, but he does bug them and want to play so best with no cats or very dog savvy cats. He is doing well on house and crate training. He needs a family who understands he is a senior and will eventually have a hard time with stairs. 

Thank you for reading about our awesome dog. All dogs came to us from different situations and we often do not know much about their past, but they are rescue dogs who deserve a second chance and need patience on their journey. All of our dogs our are in foster homes all across the bay area. 

The first step of the process is you must submit an application in order to set up a meet and great or talk with the foster family. Once application is submitted the foster parents will contact you to chat more about the dog and make sure they're a good fit and can answer any further question. The application answers most of all of our questions and can best match you. If you do not get the dog you apply for we can use your same application for 90 days towards another dog in our care and simply forward your app to that foster parent. 
http://form.jotform.com/underdogca/dog-adoption-application

All dogs will be fully vetted (Spay/ Neutered, Micro chipped, DHPP and Rabies Vaccinated) and other possible vet care prior to adoption.

The adoption fee is $300, which is considered a non refundable donation

visit us at underdogca.com or follow us on FB and IG @underdogca
https://www.facebook.com/underdogCA

animal.description: This handsome, young boy is definitely a work in progress. Robin is 8 months old and currently weighs 52 pounds. His many attributes include being very smart, lots of energy and a great adventure buddy. Because he is extremely energetic and still working on some much needed manners, Robin will need an adopter that is totally committed to long term positive training which include classes as well as in the home. Robin may look like an adult, but is still very much in puppy mode especially in the home, so his adopter will need to have the flexibility to tweak his training plan as the need arises. Robin is an enthusiastic learner, but will need lots of exercise/playtime to burn off that energy, which will help him focus on training. When he feels settled, he will be a great snuggle friend. This boy enjoys playing with other dogs and should have a good buddy that does not live in the home. He will most likely be able to live with another dog in a few years, but for now he should be the only resident dog in order to work on maturing into the best boy. The same applies to a cat friend, maybe in the future, but not now. Teens that can be committed to keeping Robins training plan consistent, will be considered. The shelter staff is very committed to finding the best home for this good boy and providing additional support to his adopters as needed, to make sure he is successful in the home. If you think you are a good fit and would like to learn more, please fill out the form in the link below. mspca.org/nevinsadoptioninquiry

animal.description:
Hi meet Benji, 

Benji is a Pointer Bulldog his 3 years old. He loves playing with with his human friends and toys. He is an amazing snuggle buddy. Benji is a sweet and energetic boy with everyone he meets. He is supper excited to find his forever home. 

We hold an event every weekend at our facility on SATURDAY 11-5pm.   Please visit our social media platforms for the specifics for each weekend as it changes from week to week. Please find our application at lovejoyfoundation.org when you come to an event please bring that filled out in hand with you. You can find our application at Lovejoyfoundation.orgYou MUST submit an APPLICATION via email in hopes to get an appointment, our application is found on our website lovejoyfoundation.org. If you do not get a phone call by Friday then we did not have anything available for you or the pet of interest was adopted before we got you application. We are a Southern California based rescue and do nothing adopt further than an hour from our headquarters in Inglewood, Ca. we do not adopt out more than a 30 minute radius. We appreciate you being understanding and Patient as we attempt to go back to a new normal.

animal.description:
Meet Peeps! 

This 2 year old was an owner surrender in the south. Why? We do not know. Peeps is a perfect size at 30lbs and is pretty darn cute. He is also loyal, following you wherever you may go. He would love to find a new family. A family who will keep him forever. mapawsmepetrescue.com

Interested in meeting Peeps? 

All Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue dogs are in homes with foster families; we do not have a shelter where dogs are available for daily viewing.

Our process is as follows:
1.  Review our policies and adoption radius  on our website: http://mapawsmepetrescue.com/adopt/
2.  Submit an application for review and approval;
3.  MPM Rescue reviews application and checks vet records and references;
4.  MPM foster contacts approved applicant(s) to arrange a home check and meeting with available dog(s);
5.   If there is a good fit, adoption is completed with a contract and fees (payable via check or cash).

The adoption fee is listed here: http://mapawsmepetrescue.com/adopt/

Dogs from Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
- Spay/Neuter surgery
- Age appropriate vaccinations
- Heartworm test (for dogs over 6mo) and treatment if positive
- Microchip
- Deworming
- Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
- Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

*Please note that the identified breed(s) are best guesses. We very rarely have information on our dogs' actual breeds since they often come to the shelters we work with as strays.*

animal.description:
Winifred is such a happy girl. She loves her toys more than anything in this world and will parade around carrying a toy, showing you how proud she is of it! It is the most adorable thing ever. She is skittish around new people and takes some time before she trusts you, but is a very loving and gentle girl. She would prefer a home with other dogs who will help her feel more confident. She is medium energy and likes to run around in the backyard from time to time but mostly hangs out on her bed and follows you around. She has a good spirit and will make a good addition to a patient family, as long as they have lots of toys for her!

Winifred is only available for foster-to-adopt at this time. She is heartworm positive and will need to get started on her treatment soon. All medical expenses are taken care of by the rescue when the dog is in foster-to-adopt care. Winifred will have no lasting health issues as a result of her heartworm status. She will be a normal, healthy dog!

animal.description:
Sweet Pollie is a year old Dachshund mix boy who just LOVES to play! He and his brother Rollie have been together their entire lives and were taken in by a sweet woman in East Texas who has done her best to give them what they need. They are just stronger and more playful than she can handle, so she reached out to us to help find them a wonderful home. We would love for them to stay together or at least have another dog friend to live with.

Pollie, who is a little smaller than his brother, wants a very affectionate family with bigger children or a younger active couple. He is very loving, but strong and active. Both Rollie and Pollie are potty trained and need either a fenced yard to run in or someone who can take them on active walks daily.

If you would like to meet Rollie or Pollie (or both), please fill out an adoption application at www.northstarpets.org and be sure to mention the name of the dog you'd like to meet!

animal.description: Meet Garnet, totally cool, freaking adorable and ready for her new forever home! Garnet gets along well with other dogs and would love another dog to play with.  What a great face and those gorgeous eyes! As always, we aren’t sure at all about her breeds- but we know Garnet is energetic and loves to be active.  She will make a great exercise partner and is getting very good on the leash.  Garnet was rescued by Jillian of Training to the Rescue and working with Jillian has been great for this smart and curious babe.  Garnet likes hanging out her daycare.  She gets doggie time and training time, but really is longing for her own family time most! Two-year-old Garnet weighs just under 57lbs and would enjoy visits to the dog park or daycare.  She’ll make a great exercise partner as she loves the outdoors and is ready to accompany you on any and all adventures.   Garnet would benefit from your dog experience as well as your continued training.  Such as “pleaser” she can’t wait to make you happy! Garnet is affectionate, loving and definitely enjoys her people time. She loves kids as well as dogs, but kids should be older as she is fast and might knock a little one down.  Garnet is good in the car, crate trained and house trained. Her beautiful brindle spotted coat is ‘easy care’ like her! She would love a fenced yard but would be fine with urban living as long as her people were active and got her out and about. But no kitty siblings for this girl. Playful Garnet is enjoying learning games as well as tricks and training- we think she would be great at doggie sports too.  Garnet would be very content at the end of an active day to curl up on the sofa and spend all of her time with you!  She is spayed, micro-chipped and vaccinated and can be visited with her foster mom Jillian. Garnet’s adoption fee is $250 and she is ready and deserving of a truly wonderful home. You just have to meet this adorable and fun-loving girl! Please complete an online application for Garnet at: https://www.emailmeform.com/builder/form/N1V88edh02ForIB30gCf2. Or for questions, email Jillian at trainingtotherescue@gmail.com.  Get ready for fun and action as well as lots of LOVE and loyalty with grateful Garnet!
animal.name: Garnet, playful pretty pleaser!

Our adoptions come with a one week trial period in which if things are not working out, we will refund your adoption fee if you decide to return your newly adopted Faithful Friend. Our adoptions must be done in person and we do not arrange transport to adopters. Our adoption fees vary and we are only able to accept payments by card* at this time but include spay/neuter, heartworm test (dogs), FeLV/FIV test (cats), age appropriate vaccines and deworming, flea, tick and heartworm medication and microchip.

animal.description:
Jack is such a handsome dude!  He is estimated to be between the age of 1-3 years old and weighs 43 pounds. 

What a goof, as you can see, he loves to run and play!  Jack is enjoying life now, which is great, as he came to us heart worm positive and had to take it easy for a while.  He has successfully finished his treatment and is ready to find his forever home.  It would be wonderful if he could find a fun and active home, he loves to be on the go and exploring.   Jack has an independent flair too and can entertain himself if he were to have a big back yard, just using his nose and having lots of things to investigate. 

Through no fault of his own, he doesn't appear to have been taught the necessary skills for him to flourish (boundaries, obedience), but with strong leadership, he is smart enough to learn them.  Strong leadership and direction would help this zany boy learn the necessary skills he needs to blossom in a home.   Jack would thrive on not only physical exercise, but also on exercises for his mind, such as nose work and treat puzzles.  Jack is connecting, silly and fun, he is so worth the time if someone could show him the way.   

Jack does need to go to an adult only home though, due to the fact that he has some food bowl and rawhide guarding.  He will need an experienced adopter who can continue to work with him on this.  He will also need a home with a fenced in yard that is at least 6 foot high, as we have discovered he is quite the jumper.  With his curiosity and houndy nose, we want to keep him safe. 

If you are interested in Jack and are at least 21 years old, please fill out an application at K9stray.com and we will be in touch.

Adopters must live within a 100-mile radius of Joliet, IL to be considered. The adoption fee is $425. This covers all shots, spay/neutering and microchip.

To be considered for this dog. Please fill out an application here: https://www.pawsup4rescue.org/dog-cat-applicaiton

Our adoption process typically takes from one to two weeks. When you find an animal you are interested in, we ask that you fill out an application as a first step so we can determine if your family is a good fit for the animal. If you are, then we will contact you to arrange a time for you and your family to meet the animal so you can decide if it is a good fit. If you currently have dogs, we require that the dogs be present at the meeting to make sure it's a good fit all around. Once compatibility is determined, we move on to the paperwork and finalizing the adoption. 

If the meet is not a good fit, we will keep your application on file for up to 1 year and we will gladly consider your family for another dog. 

Follow us on FACEBOOK: www.Facebook.com/PawsUp4Rescue/ 
and on INSTAGRAM: www.Instagram.com/Paws_Up_4_Rescue/

animal.description:
Buster is a very good boy! He is 8 years young, and despite a sedentary beginning he has decided that running is fun, (but only for short periods of time). He loves his daily walks more than anything (well, expect food, and his people). Buster’s original owner was an older man who, sadly, had to move into a nursing home due to dementia. During this process, Buster was left in a boarding kennel for 5 long months. Eventually, the family decided that no one wanted to take in this sweet boy, so he is now single and looking for a long-term commitment. Before going to a home, Buster’s owner often forgot that he had already been fed, so Buster is currently on a weight loss program. He is down to approximately 80 pounds, but still has a few more to go. Fortunately, he loves walking and playing.  Despite being an only dog for his entire life, Buster has realized that having dogs around if fun (as long as they don’t try to eat his food!) and is learning how to play for the first time. He has been around cats his entire life and doesn’t seem to mind them. He likes children when he meets them on the street but has never lived with kids in the home before. As an older fellow you don’t have to worry about potty accidents or inappropriate chewing. He loves to play but is also happy just settling down by your feet for a nap. This guy is a champ! He is polite and good on a leash. He is not currently being crated, but he is such a good boy that it hasn’t been necessary.  Buster is now ready to start a new adventure with his new family.  He is so deserving of a family of his own and will make an excellent companion.  Do you have room in your home and heart for Buster?

Are you interested in adopting Buster or another JCAPL pet you have seen? You'll need to start by completing an adoption application, available online at our website: www.jcapl.org. There is no obligation to adopt by completing an application, however, we do recommend submitting an application as soon as you find an animal you are interested in. We review applications in the order they are received.

Completed applications can be sent via email to adopt@jcapl.org , faxed to 919-300-5524 or delivered in person by visiting us at one of our adoption events on Saturdays at PetSmart in Garner (White Oak Shopping Center). 

We will contact you as soon as possible once we receive your application.

Thanks for thinking adoption!

animal.description: 01/23/21 Spirit returned to the shelter as a stray after getting loose from her owner almost immediately after being adopted. Spirit was on the lam for almost 2 weeks before a citizen was able to get ahold of her and return her to the shelter. During that time, Spirit had been periodically returning to the owner's home to eat food that was left out for her, but she would not come inside or allow herself to be caught. Despite being quite friendly at the shelter, Spirit should still be considered a skittish dog, who, if left off leash or uncontained, WILL RUN. Spirit's adoptive owner did not elect to redeem her, so she is available for adoption again, but she will need an extremely vigilant owner who will keep her on leash, inside, or otherwise appropriately contained (a chain and dog house or a secure run) at all times. A fenced yard may not be adequate, particularly if she is unsupervised. We have heard from two other adoptive owners that adopted dogs from this group. One dog appears to be adjusting well into his home, the other dog was lost. PLEASE ask a lot of questions and do research on Alaskan Huskies prior to adopting Spirit. We at the shelter like her very much, but she should not be considered a 'normal' house pet at this time. Spirit does keep her kennel clean! 12/29/20 Spirit was surrendered to the shelter because her previous owner could not take care of her or many of the other dogs they had. She has lived outside her entire life and will need help adjusting to be an indoor dog. We do not know if she is trained for mushing or skijoring. She does not know any commands, and does not know her name. She needs a kind and patient person to work with her on some basic doggy skills. When first meeting her she can be shy and reserved, but is easily won over with good treats and sweet words. She is incredibly sweet and affectionate to her animal tenders and loves getting petted. She does like to jump up on people when she greets them and give them a hug. Spirit likes the company of other dogs and does get a little sad if she is the only dog. We do not know how Spirit will do with cats, or other small pets. She is an Alaskan Husky, who are known to have high prey drives, so please take caution when introducing any other animals to her. Spirit is an escapee, and will need to be in a fenced yard or kept on leash when outside so she does not go on the run! Spirit is here patiently waiting for a special someone to give her a loving forever home.

animal.description:
In memory of Mike and Laura Bysiek.Sisters Jean (Mike) Gonska and Lorraine (Larry) Diggs, wanted to leave a lasting legacy in memory of their loving parents by establishing the Mike & Laura Bysiek Memorial Fund at the Cattaraugus Region Community Foundation to support a number of nonprofit organizations in the community each year.
As long-time active volunteers at Joyful Rescues and seeing the amazing, awe-inspiring, life-saving, tireless work that is done every day there, it was a wonderful option to be able to sponsor a life-saving pet transport annually in their honor.
Mindy was born around September 7, 2020, and might top out in the 15-20 pound range. Mindy was surrendered to a high kill shelter in the south along with 11 other dogs from the same home. For breeds, we feel they are mostly Chia/Terrier mixes but there are likely a dozen more breeds mixed in. They get along wonderfully with the other dogs and have sweet, happy, dispositions. You will likely have some housetraining to do but it shouldn't take long as they seem eager to please and are smart little cookies. This is all we know so far and we will be learning as we go and so will you!
The Adoption Fee for this dog is $500.00
Adoptions fees vary based on adoptability. In general our fees include spay/neuter, all age appropriate vaccines, Home Again micro-chipping & registration, worming & flea control - a 'complete' pet. We accept CASH or Visa/Mastercard ONLY.

Joyful Rescues has no funding except for our adoption fees and miscellaneous donations. Pet care and vet bills are expensive - you must be ready to take on this financial (as well as emotional) responsibility. YOU MUST BE AT LEAST 25 YEARS OF AGE TO ADOPT A DOG FROM JOYFUL RESCUES

We keep our pet list as up-to-date as possible. As soon as a pet is adopted, it is removed from the list. If a pet is still showing, it is still available for adoption.

Can't Adopt Me? SPONSOR ME
Look for the Link 'Special Instructions to Seller' if you want to note a particular pet
Before you seek to adopt a pet from Joyful Rescues, please read our Pet Adoption page http://www.joyfulrescues.org/pet_adoption.html.

Online Application

animal.description:
Meet STORY - she's about 1.5 years old and her story is that she was seen being pushed out of a car in a parking lot and someone picked her up and took her in. They connected with one of our volunteers and after looking unsuccessfully for an owner she came into our rescue.

STORY is a young, athletic dog with a high prey drive. She is smart and listens well to a strong, confident leader. She is a rough and rowdy player with dogs and is learning how to play nicely - just like with humans, she would do well with an older confident dog who can teach her some manners.  STORY is unlearning some bad "puppy" habits like jumping up and mouthing so we suggest a home with no kids or high school aged and above. 

STORY is spayed, microchipped, vaccinated and crate-trained. She weighs about 60lbs. 

See additional video: https://www.instagram.com/p/CKAF9lZn7YD/

If you are in the Los Angeles area and interested in meeting STORY, please fill out our brief online questionnaire (copy and paste link): www.downtowndogrescue.org/adoption-questionnaire

Additional Downtown Dog Rescue information email: adopt@downtowndogrescue.org or call: 818-407-4145
