animal.description:
Windy would be the perfect dog for a calm homebody that just wants a snuggle buddy to keep them company. She gets nervous with too many people around and prefers a quiet home where she can really connect to her people. She takes time to come out of her shell, but you will feel very special once she lets you in. Windy has lived a long, hard life and just wants a family who will let her retire with them. Though she is older, she has a forever puppy face and doesn't have any health concerns. She is low maintenance and low key. Windy is the perfect dog for an older person who wants a companion. 

Windy is comfortable around all dogs and is also compatible with cats. She is completely vetted and not on any medications/supplements. Windy was living in an abandoned house with 43 other dogs before she was rescued, so you can understand how living in a real home is a whole new experience for her. She is being fostered in Fort Worth, TX.

animal.description:
Koda is a 7 year old Newfoundland mix guy.  This big, beautiful guy is looking for someone to grow old with.  If you are looking for a lover, he is your dog... He loves to snuggle, and cuddle and spoon, he leans in and makes you feel loved and warm and comfy surrounded by his thick beautiful fur. He will do best in an all adult home or one with older respectful kids. He will get grumpy with kids (has snapped at foster’s son when he petted him on the nose) and he also likes to chase things that run. 
Koda is most happy sleeping in the room with you and he will sleep in until you're ready to get up (gotta love that!). He loves to be adored and he will adore you right back.  He likes to hang with you all day, being where you are in the house though he doesn't mind laying on the deck if the weather is nice for a nap.  And he can be left alone in the house just fine, doesn't destroy or pee, just waits. He is very strong, does pull on the leash pretty hard but we do have a new halter and leash he comes with to help with that. He sits, stays, lays down and shakes-- all very well.  He wants to do whatever you ask him to so he gets a treat or pet and he takes treats gently. 
Koda’s previous owners said he is also very protective, especially when on his property so a fence (not invisible/electric fence) is a must to protect those very important delivery drivers and unexpected guests.  A busy house with a lot of people coming and going is probably not the best fit for this guy.  With the right situation, he could make someone very, very, happy.  He will do best in a home where his humans don’t need to regularly leave him alone long hours.  In the past Koda has lived with cats peacefully.  He weighs 90 lbs. 
(A $250 adoption fee is required.) 
If you are interested in this dog, please go to the Adopt page of our website where you will find a link to an adoption application form  https://www.chewdogrescue.org/index.php/component/rsform/form/5-adoption-application-form
 
If you have previously submitted an application form, there is no need to re-apply. Just let us know you're interested in this dog. We do our best to match families and dogs so everyone is pleased and the placement is permanent. We reserve the right to refuse an applicant if the home situation is incompatible with the needs of the rescue dog. Rescue is about doing our best for the dog. We do home and reference checks.  All of our dogs are spayed/neutered, microchipped, and are up to date with current vaccinations, before being placed in their forever homes.

FOSTER HOMES NEEDED! We are always looking for good foster homes. Our rescue is foster based and we can always save more dogs if we have foster homes for them to go into. It is not a long term commitment. We have been able to find good forever homes in a short time. We also welcome volunteers who can help transport dogs and help with our outreach and fund raising efforts. Please contact us if you can help.

animal.description:
Say hello to staff favorite, Onyx!

This super hunk came to us recently as an owner surrender following a scuffle in the home with his doggy sibling and his family is moving to a place that is a little too small for him.

Onxy is looking for a FOSTER TO ADOPT family, which would not include other dogs, cats or kids under 16. We are looking for a patient family, with a lot of love and experience with the Rottweiler breed. 

Since being here at the shelter, it is obvious that Onyx is a nervous boy who lacks confidence and trust in humans. Staff has truly fallen for his gentle soul, quirky personality and eagerness to please. 

Onyx is estimated to be almost 2 years old and is a BIG boy. He is neutered, UTD on shots and will be microchipped. Due to his uncertainty and lack of trust, families must be committed to ongoing training and positive socialization in order to show Onyx that people are indeed here to love him and provide a home  of security.

If interested in giving Onyx a safe, quiet and loving home, please fill out an application at www.lebanonhumane.org and email it to info@lebanonhumane.org

animal.description:
"A good friend listens to your adventures; a best friend makes them with you!" My name is Truman and I am great at making friends, but now I am looking for my forever best friend! I am a 3 year old, 75 pound Lab mix boy. Like I said, I love making new friends and I get along with other dogs and humans of all ages. I am a playful and energetic boy who is still working on leash manners, so I am looking for an active family with a fully privacy fenced yard in which to get daily exercise (no apartments for me please). I am already house trained and, while I may not be fully kennel trained yet, it won't take a smart and eager to please boy like myself too long to get the hang of it. When I went to the dogtor, they told me that I have something called heartworms, so I have to go through treatment to get rid of those icky things, but I should be available to join your family around the end of April or first part of May! I can not wait to be your new best friend!

I am currently enrolled in the Pups 4 Parole training program and am learning all sorts of cool things to make me a great addition to your family. I need someone who will keep up with my training so I don't forget all of the cool things I am learning!

My adoption fee is $150 and includes my spay/neuter, vaccinations, wellness exam, heartworm test, and microchip! If you're interested in meeting/adopting me, please visit www.rescueonespringfield.com/our-adoption-process/adoption-application/ and fill out the form! We do adopt out of state with vet references and video home check. *Adopter is responsible for coming to get the dog and returning the dog if the adoption does not work out* 

Don't forget to LIKE us on Facebook!-www.facebook.com/rescueonespringfield

*Remember, dogs are pack animals. Because of this, Rescue One does not adopt to outdoor-only homes. Pets are family and are not disposable.  Please make sure that you are 100% committed to a pet before considering adding one to your home.

animal.description:
Meet Violet!

Violet is a sweet and smart Beagle mix pup.   She loves playing with her foster sisters and brother (dog and human).  She’s a little shy at first with new people but warms up quickly and loves snuggles, belly rubs and giving kisses.  She’s doing great with potty training and learning her basic commands.  

Interested in meeting Violet? 

All Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue dogs are in homes with foster families; we do not have a shelter where dogs are available for daily viewing.

Our process is as follows:
1.  Review our policies and adoption radius  on our website: http://mapawsmepetrescue.com/adopt/
2.  Submit an application for review and approval;
3.  MPM Rescue reviews application and checks vet records and references;
4.  MPM foster contacts approved applicant(s) to arrange a home check and meeting with available dog(s);
5.   If there is a good fit, adoption is completed with a contract and fees (payable via check or cash).

The adoption fee is listed here: http://mapawsmepetrescue.com/adopt/

Dogs from Ma, Paws & Me Pet Rescue come with the following medical care already provided:
- Spay/Neuter surgery
- Age appropriate vaccinations
- Heartworm test (for dogs over 6mo) and treatment if positive
- Microchip
- Deworming
- Heartworm and Flea/Tick Preventative
- Any other necessary medical treatment as recommended by veterinarian

*Please note that the identified breed(s) are best guesses. We very rarely have information on our dogs' actual breeds since they often come to the shelters we work with as strays.*

animal.description:
***Shelter staff wanted to point out that his photos don't do justice to his size!  He is over 100 lbs even underweight.***

This very handsome man is Raw!  Raw is a male, neutered, shepherd mix, about 7 years old.  He came to the shelter very underweight and while the scale still has a ways to go to normal he has been improving in condition.  Despite his imposing size and vocal nature this boy has been a real love with all the people at the shelter and seems to enjoy children.  Out in the yard with a ball he is joy to play with and fairly well mannered despite his somewhat goofy nature.  In the kennels he has been mostly neutral toward the other dogs.  In the play yards he has been good with most of the shelter dogs fence to fence but does respond to a direct challenge in a dominant manner.  He has paid no mind to our shelter cat or to the rooster who was temporarily housed here last week. 
 
Unfortunately Raw is heartworm positive.  Due to his age, size, severity of his heartworms and his energetic personality he will be a challenge for treatment.  We are currently working through options with our vets and would be happy to discuss those with anyone interested in placement.  Don't let the potential challenges make up your mind if you are considering Raw because this boy has the drive to make anything happen.  Please consider Raw if you are interested in adopting a wonderful canine into your family.

If you are interested in adoption please call the shelter at 530.623.1370 to learn more or schedule an appointment.

animal.description:
Meet Thor aka Trunks! He was returned to us a couple of weeks ago after the dynamic in his family changed. Thor is a neutered almost 10-month-old Redbone Coon hound mix. This boy craves love and attention. Thor does well with children who know how to be calm around dogs, he gets nervous around loud screaming kids! Thor seems a little scared of his tail being grabbed at all but does not bite he just tucks his butt and cries! Thor is such a sweet loving boy who sleeps in the bedroom on a dog bed at night and does very well with dogs of all sizes! He's super playful and loving he takes a couple of days to calm down once he's in a new environment! He is so worth the patience and love!

If you are interested in adoption; DO NOT CALL, please complete an online application on 4 Paws Animal Rescue's website at www.4pawz.org. animal.description:
Jaina came to us from south Texas early November where she was found wandering the streets malnourished. Jaina is young, around one year old and a petite little lady at 40lbs. Don’t let her size fool you, she’s a ball of fun; an active and energetic girl who loves every person she meets! Plus she can help you work from home while you work on your laptop! 

Jaina would do best as the only pet in home as she’s a bit dog selective (no cats) but may be okay with the right dog after VERY slow intros. 

Jaina is thriving in her loving fosters home - she’s ready for the next step now, finding her forever family!  Visit CaneRossoRescue.org to apply to bring this fun gal home today! 

Thanks for considering a Cane Rosso Rescue dog! 
We place dogs mostly in Texas but have adopted out a few out-of-state as well.
 
If you are interested in one of our dogs, please first complete our adoption application.
You can find it at https://www.canerossorescue.org/adoption-application . Her adoption fee is $300 plus tax. Our dogs are spayed or neutered, microchipped, vaccinated and heartworm tested and treated (if tested positive) before going to a new home. For more information, visit our website www.canerossorescue.org
or email us at rescue@canerosso.com.

We will require Danner to be in basic obedience training within 30 days of adoption. Basic obedience training is very important and a great opportunity for Danner and his family to learn new sign commands, reinforce good manners and bond with each other!

animal.description:
Available for adoption: Dasher! Miss Dasher is a 4 month old lab/hound mix who is a Parvo survivor! This girl defied all odds after being left to die in the woods- sick and alone. She came back from the brink of death and is unstoppable now! This girl is full of spunk! Her foster describes her as amazing and loveable. Dasher is super friendly and gets along with dogs of all sizes. She has not been around a cat yet. She also adores kids but due to her puppy energy- kids ages 8 and older are probably best right now. She is crate trained and working on potty training. She absolutely loves her toys and to play tug of war! If Dasher sounds perfect to you- we'd love to hear from you! Please fill out an application on our website at: www.pupandcatco.comWe do not have a shelter facility and our pets are housed in foster homes, vet clinics and local boarding facilities.

Many of our adoptable pets attend adoption events each Saturday at Mall of Georgia Petsmart in Buford, Georgia from 11:30-3:00 pm

Please check with us to find out if a particular pet will be available. Dogs going to adoption event are typically posted on our Facebook page the day prior.

Details about our adoption procedures can be seen at www.pupandcatco.com.

animal.description:
Hi I'm Dakota. I'm a 7yr old Border Collie (my foster mom believes I'm pure breed). I'm a very good dog but I've also had a rough life. Sometime last year I was dumped in a field, I found a nice old lady to cared for me until she passed and then I was surrendered to a rescue due to some of my behavior issues which my foster mom is working with me on. 

My foster mom says I'm a very good dog except I need to work on my possessiveness when getting attention (I just LOVE getting pets and attention) around other dogs. I also have an issue with getting brushed and my collar (when its off). My foster mom says that the way I react when these things are out suggests I may have had a bad experience with these objects. I tend to run and hide or growl when I can't escape. But my foster mom as slowly been working with me on these two things. I really am a sweet dog and my foster mom is teaching me to communicate without fleeing, nipping or growling. I told you my negatives now let's look at my positives! 

Since being in my foster home I've been the best dog I can be. I'm completely house trained. Never ever made a potty mess, I don't chew or destroy anything, i don't get into the trash. I take treats very gently, and I'm not pushy when it comes to meal time. I hardly jump on people and the rare times I do, I do that gently too. I love to snuggle and be with my person. I've got a very mellow personality for a 7yr old Border Collie. I am not kennel trained, and not used to being on a leash but those can be worked with. 

My foster mom is working with me on my negatives, but will suggest any family that's interested in me to look into getting a trainer to help me in my new home. 
My perfect home would be as an only dog (even though I'm good with dogs outside, I get possessive inside), and I would really like my dream home to be feline and small kiddo free. I may be a little rough around the edges but I'll make a great companion if given the chance.
If you think you may be interested in me please, put in an application in at Pawsitivetailskc.org and come meet me and see!

animal.description:
Frankie (named after Clemson's Frank Howard Field) is a sweet puppy who came to us in a litter with her 4 sisters and her 2 brothers. Her mother is a large, brown/fawn colored dog and her father is unknown. It is likely that the puppies from this litter have several different fathers because they all look so different! Our best guess is that Frankie is a Wirehaired Terrier mix and that she will be a large dog when she is fully grown. 

Most of our pets are obtained from animal control and therefore we are not certain of their breed or breed mix.  We list breed mixes that they most resemble or that their former owners said they were.  However, we don't make any guarantees about breed - it is a best guess!
To meet one of our adoptable pets or to start the adoption process, please access the adoption application on our website, www.crossroadsanimalrescue.org or download and email it to crossroadsanimalrescuesc@gmail.com. We will then approve you (sending in the application does not obligate you to adopt) and we can set up a time for you to meet one or more of our pets. You can then pay the adoption fee and officially adopt after meeting your new family member. Alternatively, you can do the adoption over the phone before meeting your new pet. The benefit to this is that we will hold the pet for you. However, the adoption fee is non-refundable if you changed your mind after adopting over the phone.

Our adoption fees include the spay/neuter surgery, deworming, vet exam, and up to date vaccines. It also includes microchipping as well as heartworm testing or feline leukemia testing. We are happy to adopt out-of-state (and even out of the country!) but transportation for the adopted pet is the responsibility of the new pet owner.

If you cannot adopt a pet at this time but would like to support our rescue, please click on the "Sponsor a Pet" button. Your donation will help feed the dogs, cats, small animals, and horses at CARE.
Please email at crossroadsanimalrescuesc@gmail.com or call us at (864)972-9906 for more information. This phone number will reach Crossroads Animal Hospital, which is the home of CARE. During business hours, a receptionist will be able to speak with you regarding our adoptable pets. After business hours, the only way to contact CARE is via email. Our puppies and kittens are also eligible for 10% off the rest of the vaccines in their puppy/kitten vaccination series at Crossroads Animal Hospital. Most adult pets are spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Puppies and kittens may have the surgery before adoption or we may have new owners return later for the surgery. For more information about CARE and to see our adoption application, go to our website, www.crossroadsanimalrescue.org

animal.description: Cornelia is back with Furkids through no fault of her own. For a short period of time, she stayed with a family until she could get back to us. She is friendly and loving and gets along well with other dogs, cats and horses. She seems to like most people and children, too. She prefers to sleep on the sofa or bed instead of a crate. Cornelia needs lots of exercise and would rather run free with her nose to the ground (she's a Hound!), so a fenced in yard is a must for Cornelia. She is currently undergoing treatments for heartworm disease. Until she has completed her treatments and is fully recovered, she is available for adoption only in the Atlanta area; she must be able to come to Furkids' shelter for treatments. Cornelia is 5 yrs. old (est. birth date 5/10/2015), 62 pounds, and her adoption fee is $275. If you want more information about Cornelia, please submit a survey at https://furkids.org/dog-adoptions/application. At this time, meeting our dogs is by appointment only. After submitting a survey, an adoption counselor will contact you to give you more information about the dog you are interested in adopting and to arrange for you to meet the dog. Must be at least 21 years of age to adopt.

animal.description:
Marley and Gizmo are a pair of bonded male yorkies. The boys are nine years old and weigh around 6 lbs each. They have been in a foster home with other dogs. Potential adopters should know that they are NOT house-trained. Marley and Gizmo are freshly groomed and just received dentals from our vet, so they are all set for a new home! To adopt this adorable duo, apply at ITVrescue.org.

All of our animals are examined by a veterinarian, given age-appropriate vaccinations, dewormed, microchipped, spayed or neutered, heartworm tested and treated if necessary.

Please realize that many of our animals are kept in foster homes. Please complete an adoption application at http://itvrescue.org/adoption-application/ in order to meet with one of our animals. There is no obligation in completing the application, but it helps us find an animal that is most appropriate for your family.  The ITV Rescue Center is open Tuesdays 12-5; Wednesdays 12-7; Thursdays 12-5; Fridays 12-5 and Saturdays 10-5.  The Rescue Center is located at 1417 N. Stockwell Road.  You are welcome to come to our rescue center during open hours to see all of our great adoptable animals. Thank you for your interest in our animals!

NOTE: Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable, so for most of the dogs we are only guessing at predominant breed or breed mix. We get to know each dog as an individual and will do our best to describe each of our dogs based on personality, not by breed label.

animal.description:
Hello I am Gabby a 3-year-old female blue nose pitbull.  I was a breeding dog until someone picked me up as a stray.  The shelter spayed me after the required 5 day holding period.  After being at the shelter for 10 days, my owner called to claim me but did not want me back because I was already spayed.  I am a high energy gal who is super smart and super sweet.  I love all people and playing ball.  Due to my high energy, it is probably best if I am in a home with older or no kids.  I do need to be the only dog in the house because I never learned to play properly, and I overreact to playing.  In addition, I am a jealous of other dogs and want all the attention for myself.  I am not reactive at all to other dogs while outside on my leash, but I am not going to be a good dog park dog.  If you are looking for a sweet gal with a lot of energy, I could be your gal!

If you are interested in meeting me please apply at www.odaatcolorado.com

Boss is a very sweet, handsome and distinguished older gentleman.
With his docked and cropped ears Boss is a low key senior MinPin who just goes with the flow.
Just a little guy at only 7lbs. he loves rides in the car, short walks , lots of treats and his blanket.
 He has a very endearing temperament. As a senior dog, he has a few typical age related issues but is still very happy and loves to be with you and cuddle or go outside with you while you garden. 
At night in his foster home he sleeps in a play pen (Ex-pen) with his favorite bed and blanket.  Boss will make a great companion pet for the few years he has left.

If you are interested in adopting Boss please go to minpinrescue.org to fill out an adoption application.
If you have any further questions or if you have already filled out an application previously please email us at: minpinfifi@gmail.com

animal.description:
Candy Litter 2020 (mom)Updated: 1/22/2021
Litter Name: Candy Litter 2020 (mom)
Brrr! I'm Lizzy, I'm about 4 years old and weigh 12 lbs! It sure is cold here in WI but I'm getting used to it and I love to wear sweaters to keep warm. I also love to snuggle and have a lot of belly rubs! Right now I live with 2 crazy Chihuahuas and cats. I like to play with the chi-chis and totally ignore the cats. I had a sleep over at a friend's house and she had big dogs. We played really well together after we got to know each other. My foster mom and everyone who meets me tell me that I am one of the sweetest dogs ever. Of course I am, after all, I'm a beautiful girl from Texas! I'm doing really well with house training. Foster mom has us all in a routine but some times it's just so cold and I don't want to go out. She makes me though, that bully! ;-) She says if chihuahuas from TN can do it, certainly a girl from TX can. I love car rides, squeaky toys, I play fetch too, and know that 'give' means to drop my toy so it can be thrown for me. I sit super nice for treats and IF I can say so myself - I have THE cutest head tilt! I am learning that being in a loving house is so much better than being pregnant and living behind a dumpster.
I need someone who wants to continue my training along with giving me belly rubs and lots of cuddles! If you are looking for a smaller bundle of joy to complete your family, I am your gal!
Adoption Fee: $475.00
We are a Wisconsin state licensed dog rescue -WI# 402433

***We do not have a central adoption center at this time. All our dogs are in private foster homes within WI. At this time we only place our dogs in areas of WI. The breed of our dogs is our best guess with the help of our veterinarians.
Our Weight Classes are as follows:
0- 25lbs - Small
26- 45lbs - Medium
46-89 - Large
90+ X-large
If you are adopting an adult dog, which we consider 6 months of age or older, your adoption fee includes the following:
Spay/Neuter, Rabies and Distemper shots, dewormed, flea & tick preventative, heartworm tested and microchipped.
If you are adopting a dog younger than 6 months of age, the dog will be up to date on the shots as per the dogs age. The dog will be dewormed, flea/tick preventative and microchipped. We only spay/neuter our dogs by 6 months of age. If you decide to adopt a younger dog than 6 months of age, they will need to be spayed/neutered at one of our preferred clinics. This will be determined by your contract along with the month they should have their surgery. This is included in your adoption fee.
Once you are approved with our rescue, you can meet any one of our dogs within the fosters home. If you are interested in the dog you met, you can take the dog home under our mandatory foster to adopt program. You receive 5 days to see if the dog is the right fit for your home.
If it is, we will conduct the home visit and finalize adoption. If it is not, it is returned to the foster. We are happy to find you another dog that meets your needs in your home.
If a dog is listed as PENDING, a family has met the dog and planning on adopting the dog after the home visit has been conducted. We always suggest sending in an application for a dog because there are times where the dogs are given back to us under the foster to adopt program. There are many reasons dogs are returned but normally it just was not the right fit for all.Please go to WWW.TAILWAGGERS911.COM under HOW TO ADOPT . We have an online application that is very easy to fill out.

animal.description:
Opie is about 4 years old and has a ton of energy! He is a very sweet boy, but he is also incredibly strong and needs to learn some manners. He loves to play with tennis balls and will chew them up if you let him. He does love to play fetch, but you have to be careful as he will jump on you and do whatever he can to get the ball. 

Opie responds very well to correction and will need an adopter that can stand their ground with him. He does very well with correction. He also knows a couple basic commands. He has proven that he is a smart and knows how to "sit"! He sat beautifully for his picture as you can see! 

He does need some work, but with the right adopter he will go far! Opie is very housebroken when taken out regularly. 

Opie loves treats and will do anything for them! His cage presence is a little overwhelming when people come to visit, but he is a great dog outside of his cage. We think that he would be okay with older children, but he is just too strong for small children.

animal.description:
This is Delilah! She’s an 11 lb chihuahua mix. We think she’s 1-2 years old. We’ve gotten rabies shots and all inital vaccinations. She has the prettiest honey brown eyes and is a major snuggler. She loves nesting on top of piles of laundry and following me around the house like a little shadow. She’s housebroken, great on a leash, and doesn’t have any major behavioral issues we’ve encountered thus far. She definitely gets along well with other dogs but is quite an independent young lady. I think she’d do well in a household with or without dogs, with or without children. Overall, this gal is super easy going and is so sweet, no doubt whoever meets her will fall in love with her. This sweetheart is ready for a forever home! 

This dog is a Benefactor Dog. His/her increased adoption fee will allow them to act as a benefactor to other dogs in our care that require special medical care and a better chance at adoption.

If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (that application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

 The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information.

2021 Adoption Fee Scale:
Benefactor Puppies under 12 months - $500
Benefactor Dogs over 12 months - $400


*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

If you elect to contact us via e-mail it may take several weeks for us to get back to you.  Renters must provide proof that you are allowed to have a dog. Is there room in your heart for this sweet little dog in need? Helen is diabetic and being held in a vet clinic after being surrendered by her owner.  The owner could not afford treating her diabetes so just ignored it.  Diabetes is not something that can be ignored without consequences and the consequence for this little girl is she has very limited eyesight.  She does best in familiar places where she knows where things are.  The people at the vet clinic say she is just the nicest girl and they are hoping we can find a home for her.  She is about 6 years old and weighs about 35#.  She is in South Dakota and will be transported to Saint Paul if we can find a home for her.   PUP will cover the cost of insulin for Helen for two years.   

Helen has been vet checked, wormed and vaccinated. PUP will have her spayed prior to placement.

animal.description:
Bowie is a female approximately 8-10 month old 45 lb mixed breed (possibly catahoula, lab, heeler) found after being dumped on the side of the road. This sweet girl is a little shy at first, but after a few minutes getting to know you, she is the friendliest pup. She loves fetch (seriously, she will play for hours if you don’t get tired), going on walks, and snuggling on the couch. She wants to go everywhere with her foster family and LOVES the car and sticking her head out the window. She does not chew, but definitely benefits from having a few toys around to play with. She is great with other dogs and has been around a cat and was curious, but not reactive. Unknown how she would be with kids, but given her calm nature, she would likely do well. Due to being abandoned, Bowie does not like being without a companion or left alone, so she would do best with a family who can give her lots of love, attention, and play time. Bowie is spayed and heart worm negative. This amazing girl has had a tough first few months of her life and is ready to settle down in her forever home!This sweetheart is ready for a forever home!

Please note: as with most rescue puppies, we have no way to guarantee this puppy’s breed or size potential. 

*Take Paws Rescue saves dogs from high-kill shelters in Southeast Louisiana, owner surrenders, and discarded dogs with uncertain futures. All of our puppies live in foster homes where they are socialized, and well cared for. An application will be required to make sure it’s the perfect match!

 If you are interested in meeting and/or adopting, the first step is to please visit our website to complete an application and read all of our FAQs: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/adopt 

**An inquiry/question on Petfinder is NOT an application. All known details about our animals are posted on their profile and updated daily. Other info would be discussed in detail with the foster during the application review process. Due to the number of inquires received (hundreds daily) we ask you submit an application on our website (a single application can be used for any dog with Take Paws Rescue).

The adoption fee for adult dogs covers age appropriate vaccinations, microchip, spay/neuter if not yet performed, heartworm test & appropriate heartworm treatment by the rescue's vet. All dogs in our care are also kept up-to-date on HW/Flea Prevention. Please see our website for more information. 

2021 Adoption Fee Scale for non-benefactor animals:
Puppies under 12 months - $300
Dogs over 12 months - $200

For additional information, including the adoption process and our adoption fee scale for all our adoptable pets, see our FAQs page: https://www.takepawsrescue.org/faq

*Any breed labels used by Take Paws Rescue, its employees/volunteers, or on vet records provided cannot be guaranteed.  Breed labels are given based on information obtained during intake and/or best guesses based on appearance and/or temperament of the dogs and Take Paws Rescue gives no assurance to the accuracy of these labels. Labels are necessary for postings to many animal networking sites, such as Pet Finder, and are no way a guarantee. Additionally, exact age and potential size cannot be guaranteed.

animal.description:
“Hi, my name is Bella!  I’m 13 years old and full of Love.  I came to my foster home in rough condition, but look at me now!  I am ready to find my furever home!  I Love everyone I meet, dog and kid friendly.  I would prefer older respectful kids though.  I don’t know if I like cats or not, whatever those are. I am housebroken.  I love car rides, playing with my foster sister, toys and I especially love my bones.  In my downtime, I enjoy being on my person’s lap or lounging in my bed.  I am still a little itchy because of my skin condition and I am looking for someone that will continue with my weekly medicated baths, ear wash and ear drops.  I do take Apoquel daily. If you have room in your heart and home for me, the link to fill out an application is below.”

Our adoption process starts with our application. Once the application is approved, a member of Legacy will contact you to set up a home visit. The home visit usually last 1-1 1/2 hours and is to make sure our dog and any current dogs/cats are getting along, as well as both of us agreeing it's a fit. At this time the adoption fee is due, and begins the 2 week trial. We will check in during the 2 week trial. If it's not working, our dog is returned to the foster home and all except $100.00 {$75 if Senior} of the adoption fee is returned. At the end of the 2 week trial, you decide if you will finalize the adoption - if finalized, the Adoption Contract is signed and all medical records are turned over to you. If at any time you need to rehome the dog it contractually needs to be returned to Legacy Dog Rescue.

ADOPTION FEE's:
Puppies under 6 months:  $199.00
Adults:  $150.00
Seniors (over 7 yrs):  $99.00

If you are interested in one of our dogs please fill out an application: 
https://form.jotform.com/193425528783165

animal.description:
Meet Scooby! This adorable Pitbull mix is looking for his forever family. Scooby is a high energy, fun loving puppy who is loves to spend time in the great outdoors. Scooby has a goofy, gregarious personality, and will definitely keep is people laughing with his puppy antics. He would love for his new family to take him on long walks at the park, and throw the ball for him in the backyard each day. Scooby loves to play fetch, and does a good job bringing the ball back after each throw! 

Scooby is an active, rambunctious fellow who needs a family ready to spend the time and energy needed to teach him all the things "grown up" dogs need to know. He is a clever pup, and would benefit from training classes to help him channel all his energy into becoming a model canine citizen. This sweet boy is treat motivated, and eager to please. 

His foster reports, "I would say Scooby is definitely a people person - he loves being next to his me at all times and loves physical touch. When sitting on the couch, he loves to lay on my lap or sit next to me and be as close as possible. Scooby likes to have naps during the day and will do so either on the couch next to me or on his dog bed. He also LOVES to cuddle with me in bed."

Scooby is reported to be house broken, and his foster reports he has good home manners. Because Scooby's manners around people when he gets excited are a work in progress, he will do best in a home with teenage children. His foster says, "Overall, Scooby has surprised me at well behaved he is. He is a very loving dog and just wants to be with me at all times during the day." 

With a bit of time and patience, this dashing puppy will be a fantastic canine companion to whichever family is lucky enough to adopt him. If Scooby sounds like the right fit for your household, schedule an adoption appointment today!

animal.description:
Burt is just the man! He is truly a fabulous dog rescued from St Frances Shelter in South Carolina. Our understanding is that once hunters no longer need the animal or he/she isnt hunting properly they leave them in the woods to fend for themselves :( 
Burt is estimated to be about 10 years old, 42 pounds and fully vetted.
Burt loves to play with dogs and kids. He doesn’t mind cats. He runs up smiling for pets and his missing bottom teeth pop out adding extra character to this gentle elder.
Burts days consist of playing and napping. He is a wonderful family companion. Burt does have a tendency to dig so a fenced yard is preferred with a family who will oversee him at all times. He was so happy to show his foster dad how he got into the neighbors yard :) since he does so well with cats, dogs and kids, those applications will be considered first.
Burt will counter surf so basic training classes are highly recommended.
Our application can be found on our website on the available dogs page.
Thank you!
